<L>__{interior house night}
<A>__{william moves down to the room where his uncle would be sleeping. he opens the door. the bed has been slept in but his uncle is not there. he moves downstairs to}
<B>__{the kitchen}
<A>__{but his uncle is not there either. then william hears a strange, haunting sound distant, carried by the wind. he moves to the window and sees only moonlight. he opens the window and hears it more clearly: bagpipes. william lights a candle and throws open the door. wind rushes in, blowing out his candle. but he hears the pipes, louder in the wind.}
